Steps to Reproduce:

1.   create a Button
2.  call button's  setTitleText()
3.  call button's  loadTextureNormal()
4.  call button's getContentSize()

By normal circumstances, the expected result is the texture's size. But now, the result I got was the size of the title label.

I check the source code and I think i had find the code which may cause this bug.

After we call `loadTextureNormal()`,  it will call `setupNormalTexture()`, it will update it's size, but the `_normalTextureLoaded` flag is set after `setContentSize()` was called. This will cause the bug. 
```cpp
//at line 284 of ui/UIButton.cpp
void Button::setupNormalTexture(bool textureLoaded)
{
    _normalTextureSize = _buttonNormalRenderer->getContentSize();

    this->updateChildrenDisplayedRGBA();

    if (_unifySize )
    {
        if (!_scale9Enabled)
        {
            updateContentSizeWithTextureSize(this->getNormalSize());
        }
    }
    else
    {
     // **setContentSize() will be called here**
        updateContentSizeWithTextureSize(_normalTextureSize);
    }
// **flag is set here after setContentSize();**
    _normalTextureLoaded = textureLoaded;
    _normalTextureAdaptDirty = true;
}
```

The function `setContentSize()` will finally run to the follow code.
```cpp
//at line 638 of file ui/UIButton.cpp
Size Button::getVirtualRendererSize() const
{
    if (_unifySize)
    {
        return this->getNormalSize();
    }

    if (nullptr != _titleRenderer)
    {
        Size titleSize = _titleRenderer->getContentSize();
        /*something error here, even though we had load the normal texture but this flag `_normalTextureLoaded ` is still false.
       because it was set to true at line 301  after this function was called;
         */
        if (!_normalTextureLoaded && _titleRenderer->getString().size() > 0)
        {
            return titleSize;
        }
    }
    return _normalTextureSize;
}
```
